JOHANNESBURG - The South 32 mining company announced on Monday that it would return an additional R6.1-billion to its shareholders.It said this was part of its capital market programme, designed to maximise returns and reward shareholders when financial performance improves.The timing and number of shares purchased under the on-market share buy-back will be subject to the prevailing share price and market conditions.The buyback is not subject to shareholder approval and will be funded from existing cash reserves.The programme is expected to be completed over 12 months.eNCA